the canglang pavilion (simplified chinese: 沧浪亭; traditional chinese: 滄浪亭; pinyin: cāng làng tíng; suzhou wu: tshaon laon din, ipa: [tsʰɑ̃ lɑ̃ din]), variously translated as the great wave pavilion, surging wave pavilion, or blue wave pavilion, is one of the classical gardens of suzhou that are jointly recognized as a unesco world heritage site. it is located at 3 canglangting street in suzhou, jiangsu province, china.